{{Quote|The Force is strong here. Whether Chodo and his herd has anything to do with that, is another matter.|[[Kreia]]|<ref name="Star Wars: Knights of the Old Republic II: The Sith Lords">''[[Star Wars: Knights of the Old Republic II: The Sith Lords]]''</ref>}}
The '''Telosian Restoration Project''' was an initiative of [[Supreme Chancellor/Legends|Supreme Chancellor]] [[Tol Cressa]] to restore the ecosystem of [[Telos IV]] after the [[Planet/Legends|planet]] was rendered lifeless by [[Orbit/Legends|orbital]] [[Bombing of Telos IV|bombardment]] during the [[Jedi Civil War]]. The outcome of this project would determine the [[Galactic Republic/Legends|Republic's]] policy towards the [[Outer Rim Territories/Legends|Outer Rim]] worlds&mdash;if the project was successful, it would consider financing the restoration of other planets that had suffered from the [[Mandalorian Wars]] and the Jedi Civil War.

To monitor the Restoration Project, the massive [[Citadel Station]] was built in orbit above Telos. The project itself was guided by [[Chodo Habat]] and his [[Ithorian/Legends|Ithorian]] herd. The surface of Telos was divided into "restoration zones," each of them having a unique code, and the Republic imported lifeforms from other worlds&mdash;for example, [[cannok]]s, meant to keep the herbivore population in check, were taken from [[Onderon/Legends|Onderon]], its jungle [[Moon/Legends|moon]] of [[Dxun/Legends|Dxun]] and [[Ithor/Legends|Ithor]] itself.

By [[3951 BBY]], the Ithorians had been challenged by [[Czerka Arms/Legends|Czerka Corporation]], which, through not entirely legal means, attempted to take over control of the Restoration Project. Their plans were different from the ones proposed by the Ithorians&mdash;instead of restoring the nature of Telos, they proposed urbanizing it. In reality, they saw the project only as a cover&mdash;what they actually wanted was access to abandoned Republic military bases on the planet's surface. However, the corruption within the Czerka department on Citadel Station was eventually exposed by [[Meetra Surik]], and the [[Telosian Council]] drove the company away from Telos.

[[Kreia|Darth Traya]] predicted that the Restoration Project would complete successfully, and the surface of Telos would again harbor life for years to come. The project was still underway by [[3643 BBY]], over three hundred years later.

